---
import HomeVisitsLayout from "../../layouts/HomeVisitsLayout.astro";
---

<HomeVisitsLayout
  title="Home Visits"
  activeMainText="Is HFNY for me?"
  activeSubText="Is HFNY for me?"
>
  <h1 class="heading">Is HFNY for me?</h1>

  <p>
    If you are expecting a baby or are the parent of an infant younger than 3
    months of age AND answer YES to any of the questions below, then Healthy
    Families New York may be for you.
  </p>

  <p class="instructions">Click on the questions below.</p>

  <div id="accordion">
    <h2 class="accordion-toggle">
      Do you want to know what to expect during pregnancy, labor, and delivery?
    </h2>
    <div class="accordion-content">
      <img
        src="../images/support-worker-01.png"
        alt="Support worker with pregnant woman"
        class="float-left"
        width="15%"
      />
      <p>
        Your HFNY support specialist can provide you with information about how
        to stay healthy and feel good while you&rsquo;re expecting. She can help
        alleviate any anxieties you may have about the birth experience and
        offer techniques to assist in a smooth delivery.
      </p>
      <p class="clear"></p>

      <h2 class="accordion-toggle">
        Do you want to learn how your baby develops before birth and during the
        first years?
      </h2>
      <div class="accordion-content">
        <img
          src="../images/baby-playing.png"
          alt="Baby playing"
          class="float-left"
          width="15%"
        />
        <p>
          Babies grow so fast! Your HFNY support specialist can help you track
          your baby&rsquo;s development month by month during pregnancy and
          after birth. She can explain developmental milestones, what you can do
          to help your baby meet these milestones, and answer any questions you
          may have about what to expect from your baby as he or she grows.
        </p>
        <p class="clear"></p>

        <h2 class="accordion-toggle">
          Do you want to understand how to respond when your baby cries and
          fusses?
        </h2>
        <div class="accordion-content">
          <img
            src="../images/mom-with-crying-baby.png"
            alt="Mom comforting crying baby"
            class="float-left"
            width="15%"
          />
          <p>
            Baby&rsquo;s sometimes cry when they are hungry, wet, or tired, and
            sometimes they cry even after they are fed, changed, and rested.
            Your HFNY support specialist can teach you healthy coping strategies
            for when your baby cries and you don&rsquo;t know why. She can show
            you signs to look for if your baby may be sick and help you
            recognize when to call the pediatrician.
          </p>
          <p class="clear"></p>

          <h2 class="accordion-toggle">
            Do you want to know how to make parenting fun?
          </h2>
          <div class="accordion-content">
            <img
              src="../images/baby-bath.png"
              alt="Baby in the bath"
              class="float-left"
              width="15%"
            />
            <p>
              Feeding your baby can be relaxing, bath time can be filled with
              splashes and giggles, and playtime can provide an opportunity for
              learning and laughing. Your HFNY support specialist can work with
              you to make caring for your baby a joyful experience.
            </p>
            <p class="clear"></p>

            <h2 class="accordion-toggle">
              Do you want assistance in ensuring that your and your
              family&rsquo;s basic needs and goals are met?
            </h2>
            <div class="accordion-content">
              <img
                src="../images/sonogram.png"
                alt="couple getting a sonogram"
                class="float-left"
                width="20%"
              />
              <p>
                Your HFNY support specialist can connect you with resources in
                your community to aid with housing, healthcare, education,
                employment, and childcare. She can assist you with forms and
                processes that are sometimes confusing. She can help you
                prioritize and manage needs and demands that may seem
                overwhelming.
              </p>
              <p class="clear"></p>

              <h2 class="accordion-toggle">
                Do you want to connect with other parents like you?
              </h2>
              <div class="accordion-content">
                <img
                  src="../images/pregnant-group.png"
                  alt="Group of expectant mothers"
                  class="float-left"
                  width="17%"
                />
                <p>
                  Parenting is an important job and almost everyone can use
                  support from others who understand what it&rsquo;s like to
                  care for a newborn. Your HFNY support specialist can connect
                  you with other moms and dads in your community. These
                  connections can be invaluable in providing support and social
                  interaction for you and your baby.
                </p>
                <p class="clear"></p>
              </div><!-- end accordion -->

              <p>&nbsp;</p>
              <div>
                <p>
                  We all need a little guidance to navigate the challenges and
                  joys of parenthood. To find a Healthy Families New York
                  program in your area, please click on the map image or call
                  518-591-8610.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div>
                <h5>
                  <p class="ps-link">
                    For a complete listing of HFNY sites, click
                    <a
                      href="../Documents/HFNYSiteInfo.pdf"
                      target="_blank"
                      float="right"
                    >
                      here
                    </a> (Updated 2025-02-13).
                    <a href="../sites2.htm" float="right"
                      ><img
                        src="../images/program_sites_link.png"
                        width="50%"
                      /></a
                    >
                  </p>
                </h5>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</HomeVisitsLayout>
